-- China Stocks: Citic Securities, GF Securities, Jiangxi Boya
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-08T07:58:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/china-stocks-citic-securities-gf-securities-jiangxi-boya.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, rose 25.48 points, or 1.1 percent, to
2,420.28. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  declined 1.3 percent to 2,635.79.  Brokerages:  Citic Securities Co. (600030)  (600030 CH), China’s
biggest listed brokerage, jumped 3.1 percent to 12.47 yuan, the
highest close since Sept. 21.  GF Securities Co. (000776)  (000776 CH), the
second-biggest, advanced 2.6 percent to 30.60 yuan, a sixth day
of gains.  The People’s Bank of China, the nation’s central bank, is
assessing and studying raising the individual investment quota
for each qualified foreign institutional investor, or QFII, the
Shanghai Securities News reported today, citing an interview
with Vice Governor  Yi Gang . China last raised individual quotas
for foreign investors to $1 billion from $800 million in 2009.  Jiangxi Boya Bio-Pharmaceutical Co. (300294)  (300294 CH) jumped 55
percent from its offer price to 38.80 yuan on the first day of
trading in Shenzhen today.  Shenyang Blue Silver Industry Automatic Equipment Co. (300293) 
(300293 CH) climbed 30 percent from its offer price to 32.20
yuan on its trading debut in Shenzhen.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Chan Tien Hin  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
